        The Darryl Davies Chart, 11/07/2025; Welcome to Summer


        Hello everyone, hope you've all managed to keep up with the charts in what has been an eventful week both musicwise and weatherwise 🎹🥵 A load of new entries this week, with just three songs remaining from my debut chart (Domino Dancing, Jumanji and Ghosts Again). A strong incursion into the DDC for folk-rock duo Bear's Den, with two new entries this week at 4 & 6, and along with Depeche Mode with their new entry at 5 with Blasphemous Rumours, become the first artists with two songs in the top 10 in a single week. In addition to this, China Crisis become the first artist to have charted with three different songs, they're at number 7 this week with Red Sails, the Pet Shop Boys reach an exciting new peak at number two with Domino Dancing after a steady rise up the chart since week 1, Rudimental are up three spots to number 3, and the coveted number 1 spot this week goes to Freeez with early-80s dancefloor banger IOU, after having entered the charts on week 2. Things look poised for next week with climbers at 2 and 3, as well as exciting new entries which in theory should climb, however a debut week at number 1 for Freeez means it won't be an easy battle for this week's runner-up artists to claim top spot.


        1. IOU - Freeez (+1)

        2. Domino Dancing - Pet Shop Boys (+1)

        3. Feel the Love - Rudimental ft. John Newman (+3)

        4. Broken Parable - Bear's Den (NEW)

        5. Blasphemous Rumours - Depeche Mode (NEW)

        6. Hiding Bottles - Bear's Den (NEW)

        7. Red Sails - China Crisis (NEW)

        8. Perfect Strangers - Jonas Blue ft. JP Cooper (+1)

        9. Jumanji - B Young (+1)

        10. Ghosts Again - Depeche Mode (-5)


        As always, feel free to share your thoughts below and who you would like (or not!) to see making a challenge for pole position in the coming week 🤔👇👇

        J
